<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="phpunit.php" src="/private/var/www/paperless/wp-content/themes/paperless-agent/iSDK/src/xmlrpc-3.0/test/phpunit.php"><import line="23" module="PHPUnit/TestCase.php" /><import line="24" module="PHPUnit/TestResult.php" /><import line="25" module="PHPUnit/TestSuite.php" /><scope doc="PHPUnit runs a TestSuite and returns a TestResult object.&#10;&#10;Here is an example:&#10;&#10;&lt;code&gt;&#10;&lt;?php&#10;require_once 'PHPUnit.php';&#10;&#10;class MathTest extends PHPUnit_TestCase {&#10;    var $fValue1;&#10;    var $fValue2;&#10;&#10;    function MathTest($name) {&#10;      $this-&gt;PHPUnit_TestCase($name);&#10;    }&#10;&#10;    function setUp() {&#10;      $this-&gt;fValue1 = 2;&#10;      $this-&gt;fValue2 = 3;&#10;    }&#10;&#10;    function testAdd() {&#10;      $this-&gt;assertTrue($this-&gt;fValue1 + $this-&gt;fValue2 == 5);&#10;    }&#10;}&#10;&#10;$suite = new PHPUnit_TestSuite();&#10;$suite-&gt;addTest(new MathTest('testAdd'));&#10;&#10;$result = PHPUnit::run($suite);&#10;print $result-&gt;toHTML();&#10;?&gt;&#10;&lt;/code&gt;&#10;&#10;Alternatively, you can pass a class name to the PHPUnit_TestSuite()&#10;constructor and let it automatically add all methods of that class&#10;that start with 'test' to the suite:&#10;&#10;&lt;code&gt;&#10;&lt;?php&#10;$suite  = new PHPUnit_TestSuite('MathTest');&#10;$result = PHPUnit::run($suite);&#10;print $result-&gt;toHTML();&#10;?&gt;&#10;&lt;/code&gt;&#10;&#10;@category   Testing&#10;@package    PHPUnit&#10;@author     Sebastian Bergmann &lt;sb@sebastian-bergmann.de&gt;&#10;@copyright  2002-2005 Sebastian Bergmann &lt;sb@sebastian-bergmann.de&gt;&#10;@license    http://www.php.net/license/3_0.txt  PHP License 3.0&#10;@version    Release: @package_version@&#10;@link       http://pear.php.net/package/PHPUnit&#10;@since      Class available since Release 1.0.0" ilk="class" line="83" lineend="97" name="PHPUnit"><scope doc="Runs a test(suite).&#10;&#10;@param  mixed&#10;@return PHPUnit_TestResult&#10;@access public" ilk="function" line="91" lineend="96" name="run" returns="PHPUnit_TestResult" signature="PHPUnit_TestResult &amp;run(&amp; $suite, $show_progress = false)"><variable ilk="argument" line="91" name="suite" /><variable default="false" ilk="argument" line="91" name="show_progress" /><variable citdl="PHPUnit_TestResult" line="92" name="result" /></scope></scope></scope>